{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Util.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.withClassInstDeps\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">withClassInstDeps</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">className</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Name\">Name</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">type</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">extraDeps</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a>)</span></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">mkCmd</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Expr.html#Lean.Expr\">Expr</a> → <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Meta/Defs.html#Lean.Syntax.Command\">Command</a></span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Command.html#Lean.Elab.Command.CommandElabM\">Command.CommandElabM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Helper for deriving instances along with all dependencies.\nGiven a one-parameter class `className` and a type `type`,\nuses pre-existing conditional instances to figure out which types would\nsuffice to be implemented, then runs `mkCmd` on each type with fresh macro scopes.\n\nThe commands are generated and elaborated one at a time.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Util.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.withClassInstDeps","kind":"def","line":115,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.withClassInstDeps","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Util.lean#L115-L138"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Util.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.makeStringMatcher\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">ConfigEval</span>.<span class=\"name\">makeStringMatcher</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">discr</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Meta/Defs.html#Lean.Syntax.Ident\">Ident</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">cases</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> (<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Init/Meta/Defs.html#Lean.Syntax.Term\">Term</a>)</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">onFail</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Meta/Defs.html#Lean.Syntax.Term\">Term</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <a href=\"./Init/Meta/Defs.html#Lean.Syntax.Term\">Term</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Creates a decision tree to implement `match discr with $cases* | _ => onFail`,\nwhere `discr : String`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Util.html#Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.makeStringMatcher","kind":"def","line":17,"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.makeStringMatcher","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/ConfigEval/Util.lean#L17-L36"}}],"imports":["Lean.Elab.Command"],"instances":[],"name":"Lean.Elab.ConfigEval.Util"}